VIRAL GASTROENTERITIS UPDATE 2002 - UK & IRELAND (01)
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[The outbreaks of viral gastroenteritis included in these updates have the
characteristics of "winter vomiting disease", and are presumed to be caused
by Norwalk-like viruses (i.e. caliciviruses classified in the genus
_Norovirus_), although this is rarely confirmed microbiologically. The UK
and Ireland seem to be particularly prone to outbreaks of "winter-vomiting"
disease in institutional settings. - Mod.CP]
In these updates:
[1] & [2] Scotland (Fife and Glasgow)
[3] England (West Midlands)
[4] England (Greater Manchester)
[5] Ireland (Dublin)

